where can i get a free grant that is not a scam im trying to buy a trailer and some other things for my yr old son who has cancer and i cant find any thing but scams is there anywhere that i can get a free grant that is not part of a scam and i need it soon your best chance would be to approach charities for your year old boy nonprofits or even churches to help you out unfortunately not grants and you are finding scams because you are not going to government websites the government is not in the business of giving away free money for the sake of giving away money there are no grants for paying bills no grants for paying off credit cards no grants for getting out of debt and no grants for simply fattening your wallet grants are free but it means obligation you will be obligated to do as the grant sets out to do grants have objectives and your purpose must fit the objective of the grant for one you have to write the grant application and the grant application is not a simple document you have to explain how your purpose for applying for the grant fits well with the objectives set out by the grant there is a stringent review process through a committee you will compete with other applicants for the grant money and this grant review committee will evaluate the merits of each proposal only those that they feel exemplifies the objective of the grant will be approved you can go to the catalog of federal domestic assistance cfda http www cfda gov and grants gov http www grants gov these are two sites created by the federal government to provide transparency and information on grants browse through the listings and see if you can find any grant that would support your purposes even if you buy books on how to get grants or list that supposedly has information on grants all of them are mere rehash of what cfda has albeit packaged differently note though that these grants generally support non profit organizations intermediary lending institutions and state and local governments most of the federal grants are given to specific target groups with specific requirements e g minority business owners involved in transportation related contracts emanating from dot grant disadvantaged business enterprises short term lending program individuals especially for personal purposes are not eligible for federal grants grants are also often given to non profit groups or organizations involved in training or other similar activities grant women's business ownership assistance that are given to those who will create women's business center that will train women entrepreneurs Constitution of the Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus Security (finance) World Wide Web Capitalism Advance fee fraud American individualist anarchism Article One of the United States Constitution Microeconomics Non-profit organization Contract Divorce Life insurance Internet fraud Tax protester Civil rights Microcredit United States Postal Service Spyware Economics Fair use Same-sex marriage Commodity Windows 2000 Capital accumulation Economy of the United States Information Services Procurement Library Economy of Russia Anarchism and capitalism Money Affirmative action Freedom of information legislation Surplus value Annuity Bond OpenDocument Public domain Copyleft Information Technology Infrastructure Library Phishing FairTax Bank A Course In Miracles Business ethics Extreme Programming Intellectual property Python programming language United Kingdom corporation tax GNU General Public License Student loan Treaty Government debt Single Convention on Narcotic Drugs Poker jargon Bank fraud Judicial review Allodial title Education in the People's Republic of China Islamic banking Appeal USA PATRIOT Act International Red Cross and Red Crescent Movement Insurance Child support Separation of church and state Strategic planning Act of Parliament Peer review Leasing United States Constitution Corporate governance Libertarianism Corporate finance Conscription Business Political economy Unif